<p><b>Verilog</b>, standardized as <b>IEEE 1364</b>, is a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hardware_description_language" title="Hardware description language">hardware description language</a> (HDL) used to model electronic systems. It is most commonly used in the design and verification of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_electronics" title="Digital electronics">digital circuits</a> at the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Register-transfer_level" title="Register-transfer level">register-transfer level</a> of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abstraction_(computer_science)" title="Abstraction (computer science)">abstraction</a>. It is also used in the verification of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analogue_electronics" title="Analogue electronics">analog circuits</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mixed-signal_integrated_circuit" title="Mixed-signal integrated circuit">mixed-signal circuits</a>.</p>
<p></p>
